My area of work is mainly in technology laws (software, electronic
communications, IT contracts, free/open source software licences,
copyright, patents, personal data, etc.).

Before working as an attorney in a law firm, I have worked as a lawyer
in training at Open Invention Network and at Hewlett-Packard’s Open
Source legal center. I have also contributed to the Free Software
Foundation Europe legal efforts since 2009, as well as leading
the non-profit ISP French Data Network's litigations against
surveillance and censorship.

